WEBVTT

00:00:01.169 --> 00:00:07.209
Welcome brothers and sisters. This month we are going to focus on the beautiful

00:00:07.209 --> 00:00:13.009
Christian quality of endurance. As we watch these faith-strengthening

00:00:13.009 --> 00:00:19.570
interviews and experiences, ask yourself, what is helping them to endure? And

00:00:19.570 --> 00:00:26.010
how can I follow their example in my life? In each case, we will see the

00:00:26.010 --> 00:00:33.810
importance of always relying on Jehovah. When I prayed for comfort to calm

00:00:33.810 --> 00:00:40.049
my heart, I felt a peace come over me. This convinced me that Jehovah was

00:00:40.049 --> 00:00:45.289
truly looking after my family. And if you're made is going through a hard time

00:00:45.289 --> 00:00:51.329
spiritually, how can you help? We will consider a practical scriptural

00:00:51.329 --> 00:00:59.130
principle and how we can apply it. This is the April program of JW Broadcasting.

00:00:59.130 --> 00:01:23.489
We will start our program by visiting the South Africa branch. The work there

00:01:23.489 --> 00:01:28.329
has increased tremendously in the past few years and the branch is now

00:01:28.329 --> 00:01:35.930
expanding to support the growth. Globally, the good news is published in over

00:01:35.930 --> 00:01:41.489
800 languages. Almost 300 of those languages are spoken in Africa. The South

00:01:41.489 --> 00:01:46.010
Africa branch supports printing, purchasing, building design and audio

00:01:46.010 --> 00:01:51.170
video production in the region. Literature is printed and packed for over 15,000

00:01:51.170 --> 00:01:56.769
congregations in 20 countries. To keep up with this demand, printing and shipping

00:01:56.769 --> 00:02:01.890
teams run two shifts per day. And in peak periods, the press works around the

00:02:01.890 --> 00:02:06.689
clock. To help speed up work in the boundary and shipping departments, we have

00:02:06.689 --> 00:02:11.650
automated and mechanized many work processes. Arrangements are underway to

00:02:11.650 --> 00:02:16.490
install a second printing press but with all this increase storage spaces

00:02:16.490 --> 00:02:21.289
become very limited. So the shipping department needs a larger warehouse. The

00:02:21.289 --> 00:02:26.009
regional audio video center supports all languages in Africa with producing

00:02:26.009 --> 00:02:30.849
audio and video items. They are currently busy with an extensive training

00:02:30.849 --> 00:02:36.689
program. And soon, recording facilities will be set up in over 100 different

00:02:36.689 --> 00:02:42.810
locations on this continent. The results are wonderful. Five years ago, none of

00:02:42.810 --> 00:02:49.090
our videos were released in any of the languages of Africa. Now, 300 languages

00:02:49.090 --> 00:02:55.449
have permission to produce audio and video publications. Recently, a branch

00:02:55.449 --> 00:02:59.490
video team has been established to assist in providing video material for

00:02:59.490 --> 00:03:05.250
JW.org and for JW Broadcasting. Due to this growing demand for audio and video

00:03:05.250 --> 00:03:10.729
publications, new facilities are needed. In order to support these increases, the

00:03:10.729 --> 00:03:14.449
branch is busy with a large expansion project. Doing so in an

00:03:14.449 --> 00:03:18.889
ecologically sensitive residential area and without interrupting publication

00:03:18.889 --> 00:03:24.129
production is challenging. The first part of the expansion project is a

00:03:24.129 --> 00:03:29.169
five-story building with 48 new residence rooms. Now, this building is scheduled

00:03:29.169 --> 00:03:34.650
to be completed by May of 2015. The major part of the expansion project is the

00:03:34.650 --> 00:03:39.250
shipping warehouse. Now, this is a massive building. It's 210 meters long, 70

00:03:39.250 --> 00:03:44.530
meters wide and 15 meters high. And perhaps just to put that into perspective, you

00:03:44.530 --> 00:03:48.409
could park three Boeing 747s inside of this building.

00:03:48.409 --> 00:03:52.129
Adjoining the warehouse is an administration building that will house the

00:03:52.129 --> 00:03:57.330
regional audio video center. Included will be state-of-the-art recording studios

00:03:57.330 --> 00:04:01.889
and editing facilities. When designing these buildings, attention was given to

00:04:01.889 --> 00:04:06.729
making them environmentally friendly, energy efficient and also pleasant for the

00:04:06.729 --> 00:04:10.490
brothers and sisters who will be working inside. The concrete structure of the

00:04:10.490 --> 00:04:13.889
warehouse has been designed in such a way that in the future additional

00:04:13.889 --> 00:04:17.970
suspended slabs for officers could be added if the use of the building ever

00:04:17.970 --> 00:04:22.810
needs to change. This is what we call future-proofing a building. The branch

00:04:22.810 --> 00:04:26.449
road system is also being upgraded to allow all of the literature to be

00:04:26.449 --> 00:04:30.970
transported safely and efficiently between the countries and the new warehouse

00:04:30.970 --> 00:04:35.529
building. Rainwater running from the roads, roofs and paving all of these new

00:04:35.529 --> 00:04:40.009
buildings and areas is going to be directed into a large stormwater attenuation

00:04:40.009 --> 00:04:44.250
pond and from there the water will slowly be discharged into a local stream.

00:04:44.250 --> 00:04:48.209
Solar roof panels are being installed in various places around the branch to

00:04:48.209 --> 00:04:52.170
harvest some of the beautiful sunshine that we have and added as electricity

00:04:52.209 --> 00:04:56.970
into the Bethel power grid. The last phase of the project will be to upgrade the

00:04:56.970 --> 00:05:01.410
printer in preparation for a second manned Roland printing press. A new

00:05:01.410 --> 00:05:04.730
visitor's deck will be added and when you come on tour you'll be able to have

00:05:04.730 --> 00:05:08.689
a bird's eye view of all of the action down at the process. The building

00:05:08.689 --> 00:05:13.329
project has been contracted to several construction companies to speed up

00:05:13.329 --> 00:05:18.769
the schedule. At the peak of construction, 700 contract workers will be on

00:05:18.769 --> 00:05:23.490
site. We also have a large group of brothers and sisters from 21 different

00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:29.449
countries to assist with project management, quality control, mechanical and

00:05:29.449 --> 00:05:35.009
electrical installation and some of the finishes and builders trades. On weekends

00:05:35.009 --> 00:05:39.610
volunteers from local congregations come into a system with site preparation

00:05:39.610 --> 00:05:45.129
between the different phases. A good news reached Africa more than 100 years ago.

00:05:45.129 --> 00:05:51.850
Since then, it has grown in many receptive hearts. Currently 3.5 million

00:05:51.850 --> 00:05:57.370
Bible studies have been conducted in Africa. That is 30% of the global figure.

00:05:57.370 --> 00:06:03.490
This certainly shows that Jehovah is drawing people from every nation, tribe and

00:06:03.490 --> 00:06:12.339
tongue to bring in praise. Exciting developments indeed. We are happy to see

00:06:12.339 --> 00:06:17.740
how the kingdom preaching work is speeding up all over the world. And you may

00:06:17.740 --> 00:06:22.459
have noticed that we decided to use outside contractors to help with this

00:06:22.459 --> 00:06:28.180
particular project. Although we generally use our own construction workers, it

00:06:28.180 --> 00:06:34.300
can sometimes be beneficial to use contractors on a case-by-case basis. At

00:06:34.300 --> 00:06:42.550
times, that can speed up a project and result in savings. For a few moments, I

00:06:42.550 --> 00:06:50.350
would like to speak to you on the theme. We continually remember your endurance.

00:06:50.350 --> 00:06:57.990
What is endurance? The original language word in the Greek scriptures has the

00:06:57.990 --> 00:07:05.110
sense of standing one's ground and persevering, remaining steadfast under

00:07:05.110 --> 00:07:11.670
trial. But it means even more than just toughing it out under a difficult

00:07:11.670 --> 00:07:19.829
circumstance. The Christian who endures has genuine hope. He or she is convinced

00:07:19.829 --> 00:07:26.670
that as 2 Corinthians chapter 4 and verse 17 puts it, the tribulation is

00:07:26.670 --> 00:07:35.910
momentary and light compared with the reward which is everlasting. To illustrate

00:07:35.910 --> 00:07:42.949
the importance of endurance, you see before me a number of suitcases. Some are

00:07:42.949 --> 00:07:51.350
small, some are large. What we don't know is how heavy each one is. That depends

00:07:51.350 --> 00:07:59.550
on what's inside. Some large suitcases can be surprisingly light. Some smaller

00:07:59.670 --> 00:08:08.910
ones could be surprisingly heavy. In a sense, this illustrates what confronts each

00:08:08.910 --> 00:08:17.149
one of us when we dedicate our life to Jehovah and start out on the race for life. At first,

00:08:17.149 --> 00:08:23.829
we may not know what loads will have to carry. We may worry about what might seem to be

00:08:23.910 --> 00:08:29.990
big tests only to find that they're not as overwhelming as we feared they would be.

00:08:31.110 --> 00:08:37.429
On the other hand, some loads that we thought would be light, perhaps getting along with one

00:08:37.429 --> 00:08:45.750
another in love, might be heavier to carry than we anticipated. Then there are unexpected

00:08:45.750 --> 00:08:53.509
tests of our faith. Tests that could involve health problems, financial anxieties, family

00:08:53.509 --> 00:09:03.190
issues and personal disappointments. All such situations call for endurance. The governing

00:09:03.190 --> 00:09:10.389
body wants you dear brothers and sisters to know that we love you for your steadfast endurance.

00:09:11.590 --> 00:09:20.309
Our feelings are well summarized by Paul's words at 1 Thessalonians chapter 1 verses 2 and 3.

00:09:21.269 --> 00:09:30.149
There he wrote to the faithful Christians, we always thank God when we mention all of you in our

00:09:30.149 --> 00:09:40.070
prayers, for we continually remember your faithful work, your loving labor, and your endurance

00:09:40.070 --> 00:09:46.070
because of your hope in our Lord Jesus Christ in the presence of our God and Father.

00:09:47.029 --> 00:09:57.190
How beautifully these words convey our feelings about you. We are greatly encouraged and strengthened

00:09:57.190 --> 00:10:05.350
by your faithfulness, your integrity, and your endurance. No matter what type of hardship you

00:10:05.350 --> 00:10:15.190
are facing, two things are certain. Jehovah knows how heavy your load is and he can give you the

00:10:15.190 --> 00:10:23.909
strength to carry it. Think about that first statement. Jehovah knows how heavy your load is.

00:10:24.950 --> 00:10:31.909
How do we know that? Open your Bible to Hebrews chapter 6 and verse 10.

00:10:33.509 --> 00:10:42.470
Here the Apostle Paul, himself, a wonderful example of endurance, tells us what makes our steadfast

00:10:42.470 --> 00:10:47.429
endurance worthwhile. Hebrews chapter 6 and verse 10 says,

00:10:48.870 --> 00:10:57.190
for God is not unrighteous so as to forget your work and the love you showed for his name

00:10:57.830 --> 00:11:07.269
by ministering and continuing to minister to the holy ones. Imagine, Jehovah would consider it

00:11:07.269 --> 00:11:16.309
unrighteous to take your endurance for granted. In fact, Jehovah does more than acknowledge your work.

00:11:17.110 --> 00:11:26.870
He also helps you to carry your load. How do we know that? Open your Bible to Philippians chapter 4

00:11:27.590 --> 00:11:38.840
verses 12 and 13 and notice here what the Apostle Paul, this model of endurance, tells us.

00:11:39.639 --> 00:11:47.480
Now just before we read it, perhaps we may think of Paul as being a newcomer to the Christian faith

00:11:48.120 --> 00:11:57.240
and compared to many others, he was. But by the time he wrote to the Philippians in 60 or 61 CE,

00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:06.360
Paul had encountered many obstacles. He had many heavy loads to carry. Paul mentions a few of them

00:12:06.360 --> 00:12:13.639
in these verses, but then in the second half of verse 12, notice what Paul writes

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:23.080
in everything and in all circumstances. I have learned the secret of both how to be full

00:12:24.039 --> 00:12:30.039
and how to hunger, both how to have an abundance and how to do without.

00:12:31.320 --> 00:12:40.679
Now, notice what he says in verse 13, for all things, I have the strength through the one who

00:12:40.679 --> 00:12:49.799
gives me power. What does this mean for us? That whatever load we have to carry as a Christian,

00:12:50.600 --> 00:12:58.519
we are not doing it with our own power. Jehovah will help us carry it. He will give us the

00:12:58.519 --> 00:13:08.200
needed strength. Paul knew that because he had experienced this from Jehovah first hand,

00:13:08.200 --> 00:13:16.600
he had Jehovah's help in his life. How? Well, consider what Paul faced on his first missionary

00:13:16.600 --> 00:13:24.440
tour. An exciting assignment laid before Paul, Barnabas, and their traveling companions.

00:13:25.639 --> 00:13:33.480
Would it be a light load full of only good experiences? Or would this assignment involve

00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:42.759
challenges? Some perhaps heavier than he anticipated. Let's find out. One of Paul's first stops

00:13:42.759 --> 00:13:51.720
was Pesidian Antioch. Here, Paul and his companions had great success. In fact, the people begged

00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:58.600
them to come back on the next Sabbath to tell them more. That seems like a light load to carry,

00:13:58.600 --> 00:14:05.799
doesn't it? But Paul's return visit did not go as smoothly as he probably expected.

00:14:06.759 --> 00:14:14.279
While some accepted the good news, a poser stirred up the crowd to the extent that Paul and his

00:14:14.279 --> 00:14:23.240
companions were thrown out of the city. Paul's next stop was Iconium, about a one hundred mile

00:14:23.240 --> 00:14:33.879
or 160 kilometer trip from Antioch. Paul couldn't take a train, a bus, or a taxi. He had to travel on foot.

00:14:34.200 --> 00:14:42.200
Did things go better for him when he got to Iconium? Would his preaching there be a lighter load to

00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:51.240
carry than it was in Antioch? Well, some did accept his message, but then a poser stirred up

00:14:51.240 --> 00:15:00.600
opposition before long Paul and his companions had to flee again. This time, they walked 20 miles,

00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:09.639
or about 30 kilometers to Listera. At first, things went well there. After Paul and Barnabas were

00:15:09.639 --> 00:15:17.480
mistaken for gods, they gave a skillful witness to the people of Listera about their powerful

00:15:17.480 --> 00:15:28.039
creator. But then the imposers from Antioch and Iconium came after Paul. Some of them hated Paul so

00:15:28.039 --> 00:15:38.200
much. They walked over one hundred miles or 160 kilometers to attack him. When they found him,

00:15:38.200 --> 00:15:43.639
they stoned Paul and dragged him out of the city, leaving him for dead.

00:15:44.919 --> 00:15:51.960
Did Paul think that this load was getting too heavy to carry? Did he cave into discouragement

00:15:51.960 --> 00:16:01.080
because imposers hated him and even attacked him physically? No. Paul had endurance.

00:16:01.879 --> 00:16:10.759
And a person who endures never gives up hope, even in the face of persecution. So what did Paul do?

00:16:11.799 --> 00:16:19.879
He continued right on with preaching. This time in Derby, just imagine the effort. Paul had

00:16:19.879 --> 00:16:28.759
to exert to walk the 60 miles or about 100 kilometers to Derby the day after he had almost been

00:16:28.759 --> 00:16:37.399
stoned to death. However, the trip was worth the effort because while in Derby, Paul and his

00:16:37.399 --> 00:16:48.120
companions made many disciples. As you can see, Paul had a heavy load to carry, but he didn't give up.

00:16:48.759 --> 00:16:58.919
He continued preaching, but then Paul did something more. Open your Bible to Acts chapter 14.

00:17:00.120 --> 00:17:09.720
Here we see something that proved Paul to be a man of endurance. At Acts chapter 14 and verse 21,

00:17:09.720 --> 00:17:16.920
we read, after declaring the good news to that city and making quite a few disciples,

00:17:17.640 --> 00:17:28.200
they returned to Listera, Iconium, and Antioch. Imagine Paul and his companions walked back

00:17:28.200 --> 00:17:35.880
to the very cities where they had been viciously persecuted. Why? Verse 22 says,

00:17:36.839 --> 00:17:43.880
There they strengthened the disciples, encouraging them to remain in the faith and saying,

00:17:44.839 --> 00:17:54.440
we must enter into the kingdom of God through many tribulations. At first, that statement might seem

00:17:54.440 --> 00:18:01.960
strange. How could Paul encourage the disciples by telling them that they would have many tribulations?

00:18:02.680 --> 00:18:10.519
That prospect would seem depressing, not encouraging, but look carefully at Paul's words.

00:18:11.960 --> 00:18:20.440
He didn't simply say, we must endure many tribulations. He said, we must enter into the

00:18:20.440 --> 00:18:28.839
kingdom of God through many tribulations. In other words, Paul strengthened the disciples

00:18:28.839 --> 00:18:38.279
by emphasizing the positive result of endurance. As Jesus said at Matthew chapter 10 verse 22,

00:18:39.240 --> 00:18:46.440
the one who has endured to the end will be saved. What's the lesson for us?

00:18:48.200 --> 00:18:56.119
Endurance is not just a matter of toughing it out under a difficult situation. Endurance means

00:18:56.119 --> 00:19:03.720
keeping our hope bright in our mind. It means being personally convinced that as 2 Corinthians

00:19:03.720 --> 00:19:14.920
chapter 4 and verse 17 says, the tribulation is momentary and light, but the reward is ever lasting.

00:19:16.119 --> 00:19:21.880
Would you like to see how some of your brothers and sisters are displaying that kind of endurance?

00:19:22.839 --> 00:19:30.200
We'd like to introduce you to brother Vasili Kalin, who was baptized for more than 50 years

00:19:30.200 --> 00:19:37.480
and serves together with his wife Maria at the Russia branch. Has their load been easy to carry?

00:19:38.599 --> 00:19:51.660
This is their story. I was born in Ukraine to a family of Jehovah's Witnesses. When I was five,

00:19:51.740 --> 00:19:58.299
our whole family was exiled to Siberia. Traveling in the same train was a little girl who 17

00:19:58.299 --> 00:20:04.859
years later would become my wife. That was Maria. We were married in 1968.

00:20:11.450 --> 00:20:17.289
Under the Soviet Union, there was a ban on importing our publications. The congregations needed

00:20:17.289 --> 00:20:23.289
more literature and we wanted to help the brothers. So Maria and I decided that we would start printing

00:20:23.289 --> 00:20:30.569
the publications ourselves. I knew it would be risky because we had two young children.

00:20:30.569 --> 00:20:37.450
Our son was then only five years old and our daughter was less than a year old. We risked losing

00:20:37.450 --> 00:20:45.690
our freedom and even our children. But we trusted in Jehovah to support us and we didn't think too

00:20:45.769 --> 00:20:50.970
hard about what could happen. If we have done that, we would just have given up.

00:20:54.569 --> 00:21:00.410
My biggest problem was that I had no experience with photo development whatsoever.

00:21:01.450 --> 00:21:05.289
So what did I do? I bought a reference book and some equipment.

00:21:07.930 --> 00:21:12.730
The circuit of the year gave me the microfilm that was used for duplicating literature.

00:21:12.730 --> 00:21:19.769
Then one evening we tried printing the literature for the first time. Of course it was a complete mess.

00:21:19.769 --> 00:21:25.450
But in a little while we were able to start producing publications that were of good quality and

00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:34.490
readable. Our work was highly confidential and we had to keep it a secret even from our family

00:21:34.490 --> 00:21:40.890
who were all witnesses. Our work was done at night. We closed our curtains and turned off the lights.

00:21:40.890 --> 00:21:43.930
We had a red lamp that gave us light while we were working.

00:21:44.890 --> 00:21:49.450
When the literature was ready, we would deliver it in the morning to all the congregations.

00:21:50.890 --> 00:21:55.769
It was also difficult and dangerous because if they caught us with literature,

00:21:55.769 --> 00:22:01.849
there was no doubt we would be sent to prison. We needed to travel dozens of kilometers.

00:22:02.490 --> 00:22:08.569
I am very grateful to Maria that she often helped me. A brother would drive up in his car and

00:22:08.569 --> 00:22:14.730
I would pass on the literature to him. One time the brother was late. In Siberia it gets very cold.

00:22:15.609 --> 00:22:21.609
And I remember that it was snowing so heavily that I turned into a snow woman you could say.

00:22:21.609 --> 00:22:26.329
I couldn't go into a store to wear a mom because the brother could come any minute and we would miss

00:22:26.329 --> 00:22:28.569
each other. So I had to wait.

00:22:30.569 --> 00:22:35.769
When I would come back from work and Maria wasn't home, I would get very worried.

00:22:35.849 --> 00:22:38.730
Anything could have happened. Maybe she had been arrested.

00:22:39.849 --> 00:22:45.210
Sometimes our children knew that mama was a way to deliver in literature and they also got worried.

00:22:48.089 --> 00:22:55.769
Everything I have gone through has taught me never to rely on myself but instead to completely trust

00:22:55.769 --> 00:23:02.650
in Jehovah. We got a lot of joy out of the years we spent producing literature.

00:23:03.289 --> 00:23:10.329
We knew that our brothers and sisters were being fed spiritually. We are grateful to Jehovah

00:23:10.329 --> 00:23:14.329
that for 17 years we were able to print the publications.

00:23:16.940 --> 00:23:23.660
1991 was a landmark year for Jehovah's Witnesses in the Soviet Union. We received official

00:23:23.660 --> 00:23:30.859
recognition. What a victory that was. Unfortunately, the situation with Jehovah's Witnesses today

00:23:30.859 --> 00:23:37.099
reminds me of the time we lived through. I see that Satan's methods have not changed but it is

00:23:37.099 --> 00:23:43.740
really encouraging to remember that Jehovah also has not changed. He defended and protected his

00:23:43.740 --> 00:23:51.819
people in the past and he will do the same today. Did you notice how happy brother and sister

00:23:51.819 --> 00:23:59.900
Kalinar despite all the trials they've experienced? After all, what they went through was very serious.

00:24:00.700 --> 00:24:08.940
It's just as James chapter 5 and verse 11 says, we consider happy those who have endured.

00:24:09.579 --> 00:24:16.700
What examples of faith brother and sister Kalinar? But it's not just older ones who are

00:24:16.700 --> 00:24:23.660
showing faithful endurance. Many of you younger ones are standing your ground against opposition.

00:24:24.539 --> 00:24:32.779
For example, in South Korea, our brothers have been facing the neutrality issue since 1950.

00:24:33.579 --> 00:24:41.420
